# TEMPLATE FILE — copy into your new converter's folder and replace every
# PLATFORM placeholder with your real sample filename(s). This exact
# Input_data/Output_data pattern is required for every converter in this
# repo — see GUIDE.md "Input_data/Output_data/.gitignore convention".

# Generated output (kept out of version control)
Output_data/*
!Output_data/.gitkeep

# Input exports are site/org-specific; don't commit real PLATFORM data.
# List EVERY bundled sample file explicitly as an exception — do not
# whitelist a whole pattern. If your converter needs more than one sample
# file (e.g. cv_converter needs a nodes CSV + an activities CSV), add one
# line per file.
Input_data/*
!Input_data/.gitkeep
!Input_data/sample_PLATFORM_export.json

# Generated artifacts if ever written next to the script
ns_commands*.txt
ns_model_*.json
gen_*.csv
PLATFORM_inventory.csv
PLATFORM_report.md
PLATFORM_export.json
\[MASTER\]*.nsm
\[L1_DIAGRAM\]*
\[L2_DIAGRAM\]*
\[L3_DIAGRAM\]*
\[L1L2L3_DIAGRAM\]*
\[DEVICE_TABLE\]*
\[AI_Context\]*

# Python
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*.egg-info/
.venv/
venv/
.env

# OS / editor
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
.idea/
.vscode/
